<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - HIGH-PRESSURE OIL PUMP - Removal - Hydraulic Pump Cover</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Hydraulic Pump Cover</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The Injection Control Pressure (ICP) sensor or Injection Pressure Regulator (IPR) valve can be
                    removed before or after removing the hydraulic pump cover, if required.
                </para>
                <para>If you are removing the hydraulic pump cover, it is not necessary to remove the ICP sensor or IPR
                    valve at this time.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen three rear exhaust heat shield mounting bolts and remove heat shield.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2351102" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1311.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 414. Removing ICP sensor</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If requiring service, remove ICP sensor from hydraulic pump cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2351103" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1312.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 415. Removing IPR valve</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If requiring service, remove IPR valve from hydraulic pump cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2351104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1315.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 416. Removing the hydraulic pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove eight cover bolts from hydraulic pump cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2351105" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1316.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 417. Separating hydraulic pump cover from rear cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket scraper</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Rear cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hydraulic pump cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a thin gasket scraper to separate sealant between crankcase/rear cover seam and
                hydraulic pump cover. Do this on both sides at the rear of the pump cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, do not pry hydraulic pump cover off of pump; damage to pump could
                    occur.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2351106" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd13/D1317.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 418. Removing hydraulic pump cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hydraulic pump cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Hydraulic pump assembly</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Only after breaking sealant, lift hydraulic pump cover straight up and off hydraulic pump
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
